text.section:
The Secretary, after investigation and public hearing, may:
Establish official standards or grades for any fruit or vegetable;
Adopt rules and regulations governing the markings required on the container of any fruit or vegetable, for the purpose of showing any or all of the following:
The true grade or size of the product, or both, according to any applicable standard or grade established by the Secretary;
The name and address of the grower or packer;
The name of the state where grown; or
The variety, quantity, quality, condition, and size of the product.
